        }
      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;,serif\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 7-day-old newborn is brought to the clinic by his mother, who is concerned about the growth of extra hair on his back. Upon physical examination, the doctor observes the appearance of the child&rsquo;s back as shown in the image. To further investigate the possibility of a congenital anomaly, an ultrasound (USG) is recommended. Which of the following conditions might the ultrasound reveal in this child?</span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2023/04/30/5_LSqyXFr.jpg\" style=\"height:214px; width:291px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
