      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A 20-day-old infant is brought to the pediatric department by the mother due to a significant congenital finding on the child&#39;s lower back, as depicted in the image. As the pediatrician in charge, you examine the child and determine that surgical intervention is necessary and is scheduled for the following morning. In preparation for surgery and to care for the child&#39;s wound, what is the most appropriate immediate management?</span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cerebellum-web-static.s3.amazonaws.com/media/public/images/2023/04/30/12.jpg\" style=\"height:263px; width:227px\" /></span></span></span></p>",
